    "We contend that in order to establish the existence of such a bias, we need to demonstrate that the model consistently favors the position of a specific social group.",
    "In other words, we need to clearly distinguish between bias (a simple deviation from the truth) and social bias.",
    "The fact that we find no evidence of consistent social bias in our experiments calls for further investigations into the sources of LLM biases.",
    "They are generally attributed to the unbalanced training data.",
    "While this argument is intuitively convincing, and is supported by considerable outside of the silicon sampling literature, it cannot account for our results."
